Run on VS Code using a virtual environment (.venv).
MUST be run on 3.11.xx (I think I used .9) of Python.
Ultimately had to replicated the Codio environment originally used,
through a lot of trial and error.

anyways -
In the project terminal, 
 
cd ~
cd of project folder
py -3.11 -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate

Then 

python -m pip install tensorflow ipywidgets
python -m pip install ipykernel ipywidgets

And to install the venv as a selectable Jupyter kernel

python -m ipykernel install --user --name treasurehunt-venv --display-name "TreasureHunt (.venv)"

It was very finnicky and difficult to figure out, hopefully
it doesn't give you the same trouble if you have to run it 
because I was super unfamiliar with anything of the sort.

